# Data And Scientific Guardrails

- Do not fabricate scientific results, sample metadata, qpAdm estimates, or
  historical conclusions.
- Treat model outputs as diagnostics unless a document explicitly frames them
  as reviewed evidence.
- Preserve uncertainty, sample counts, publication keys, target notes, and
  curation decisions when transforming target data.
- Do not overwrite local `data/` files without explicit permission.
- Do not commit generated `results/` artifacts unless the user asks to promote
  them.
- Prefer cautious language: "candidate", "diagnostic", "review surface",
  "held-out check", and "posterior-predictive residual" over final claims.
- Before tuning simulator parameters to fit a target, inspect target curation,
  qpAdm uncertainty, sample-level joins, and validation splits.
- Make data filters explicit and reproducible. Avoid silent drops.
- Keep external AADR/Poseidon/ADMIXTOOLS ingestion assumptions documented in
  `docs/` and reflected in CLI help.
